      <h3>Earthquake data fundamentals</h3>

      <br/>

      <p>
          The United States Geological Survey hosts a wide variety of information regarding earthquakes on the website <a href="https://earthquake.usgs.gov/">earthquake.usgs.gov</a>.
          This tutorial will be looking at the near real time geoJson summary of past earthquakes found <a href="https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/feed/v1.0/geojson.php">here</a>.
          The data about past earthquakes is provided as geoJson. The format provides easily accessible and readible information. The key pieces of information provided for every earthquake includes magnitude, location, time and geographic coordinates.
      </p>

